        <h2>How to use these comparisons</h2>
        <p>Pick the comparison matching your shortlist, then run the VIP drop test, flash sale test, and offer discipline test on each platform. Winner is whichever enables campaign restraint during sale week — not whichever has more checkmarks.</p>
        <p>Postscript ranks first for SMS campaign execution; Attentive for enterprise promotional calendars; Sequenzy as lifecycle email layer. Read <a class="link" href="/for">vertical guides</a> and <a class="link" href="/use-cases">use-case playbooks</a> for campaign calendar context.</p>
        <h3>Campaign marketing lens</h3>
        <p>These comparisons evaluate drop orchestration, segment-by-value, offer discipline, and campaign calendar fit — not TCPA ops checklists. Noir Collective, SoleDrop ATX, and Festival Threads Co scenarios appear throughout.</p>
